  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (expanded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Following regulatory clearance, the indicated patient population was extended to include pediatric patients (body surface area 0.5–1.0 m²) and reduced-flow operating points (1.0–2.0 L/min), representing an operating envelope expansion beyond the original adult-focused validation campaign. The assessment team concluded that the prior validation dataset adequately spans the extended range on the basis of geometric and fluid-dynamic similarity arguments; no new experimental validation runs were commissioned or linked.",
