      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities cover device geometry, fluid properties, and operating conditions representative of the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation campaign used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry with bovine blood analogue at physiological hematocrit (35–40%). Operating points spanned the original adult COU (2.5–6.0 L/min, 2500–4000 RPM). The expanded pediatric COU (1.0–2.0 L/min) shares the same pump geometry and fluid properties; the assessment team concluded that geometric and fluid similarity is sufficient to assert validation relevance without additional test points. No validation activities were conducted at or below 2.0 L/min.",
